      { q: 'How does video training compare to instructor-led training in effectiveness?', a: 'Video training provides consistency that instructor-led sessions cannot: every employee receives the same information, at the same quality, regardless of who trains them or when. Video also allows employees to revisit content as needed, which reinforces retention. The most effective approach combines video modules with live discussion sessions for complex topics.' },
      { q: 'Can you produce training content for both desk-based and field employees?', a: 'Yes. Your team adjusts format, length, and delivery approach based on how employees will consume the content. Desk-based training can be longer and more detailed. Field-facing content is typically shorter, mobile-optimized, and designed for on-the-go consumption with clear visual instructions that work without audio when needed.' },
      { q: 'What types of training are most effective in video format?', a: 'Process walkthroughs, software tutorials, compliance training, onboarding orientations, and safety procedures all translate exceptionally well to video. Topics that benefit from visual demonstration or step-by-step guidance see the biggest improvement in comprehension and retention compared to text-based training materials.' },
      { q: 'How do you handle training content that needs frequent updates?', a: 'Your team builds training videos with modularity in mind. Sections that are likely to change (policy details, software interfaces, process steps) are produced as separate segments that can be swapped without re-producing the entire video. This keeps your training library current without requiring full reproductions every time something changes.' },
      { q: 'Can training videos be integrated with our LMS or internal platforms?', a: 'Yes. Your team delivers content in formats compatible with major learning management systems, including SCORM and xAPI standards where needed. Videos are also delivered in standard web formats for embedding in intranets, internal wikis, or any platform your organization uses for employee communications.' },
      { q: 'How do you ensure training videos actually improve knowledge retention?', a: 'Your team applies instructional design principles: clear learning objectives at the start, information chunked into digestible segments, visual reinforcement of key concepts, and summary recaps at the end. Videos are kept concise to avoid cognitive overload, and complex topics are broken into multi-part series rather than crammed into a single long video.' },
    ],
    relatedServices: [
      { title: 'Corporate Video Production', slug: 'corporate-video-production', desc: 'Professional corporate video from a dedicated creative team.' },
      { title: 'Educational Video Production', slug: 'educational-video-production', desc: 'Educational video that builds authority and drives organic reach.' },
      { title: 'Explainer Video Production', slug: 'explainer-video-production', desc: 'Clear, engaging explainer videos from a dedicated creative team.' },
    ],
    relatedBlogPosts: [
      { title: 'The complete guide to video production', slug: 'video-production-guide', date: '2026-02-02' },
      { title: 'Video marketing ROI: how to measure what matters', slug: 'video-marketing-roi', date: '2025-10-12' },
    ],
  },

  'educational-video-production': {
    title: 'Educational Video Production',
    slug: 'educational-video-production',
    category: 'Video',
    heroHeading: 'Educational Video Production',
    heroDescription: 'When you want to engage people and help them learn. A dedicated creative team that produces educational video content that builds authority and drives organic reach.',
    seo: {
      title: 'Educational Video Production | Moonb',
      description: 'Educational video production from a dedicated creative team. Build authority, support customer success, and drive organic reach. Predictable monthly pricing.',
    },
    serviceTypes: [
      { title: 'How-To & Tutorial Videos', desc: 'Step-by-step instructional content that teaches your audience a valuable skill or process.' },
      { title: 'Concept Explanation Videos', desc: 'Clear, engaging videos that demystify complex ideas for general or specialist audiences.' },
      { title: 'Customer Onboarding Series', desc: 'Structured onboarding sequences that teach customers how to get the most from your product.' },
      { title: 'Thought Leadership Content', desc: 'Authority-building video that positions your brand as the expert voice in your category.' },
      { title: 'Course & Certification Programs', desc: 'Progressive learning paths with modules, knowledge checks, and completion milestones.' },
      { title: 'FAQ & Help Center Videos', desc: 'Video answers to common questions that reduce support volume and improve customer experience.' },
    ],
    differentiator: {
      heading: 'The agency model is broken. We fixed it.',
      text: 'Educational video works best at the start of the customer journey — building awareness, trust, and authority before the prospect is ready to buy. Your dedicated team transforms your existing knowledge into video that attracts and educates your ideal audience continuously.',
      points: sharedDiffPoints,
    },
    stats: sharedStats,
    process: sharedProcess,
    work: sharedWork,
    testimonial: {
      quote: 'The ability to quickly understand and adapt to the company branding was impressive.',
      name: 'Diane Bizzle',
      role: 'Director of Outreach',
      company: 'Brainfuse',
      avatar: 'https://cdn.prod.website-files.com/64c4234d0856ecf478afcf82/6821b9dc6aa65e5d0a7ebe4e_Marius%20Godo.avif',
    },
    faqs: [
      { q: 'What makes educational video more effective than written documentation?', a: 'Video engages multiple senses simultaneously: visual demonstration, verbal explanation, and motion-based attention guidance work together to accelerate comprehension. Studies consistently show that learners retain significantly more from video instruction than from reading alone, especially for procedural and conceptual content.' },
      { q: 'How do you handle educational content for highly technical subjects?', a: 'Your team combines subject matter expert input with visual communication expertise. Complex technical concepts are broken into visual building blocks: animated diagrams, process flows, and progressive reveal sequences that build understanding layer by layer. Technical accuracy is verified with your SMEs at every stage.' },
      { q: 'Can educational video support customer onboarding and success?', a: 'Yes. Educational video libraries that teach customers how to get the most from your product reduce churn, increase feature adoption, and lower support ticket volume. Your team produces onboarding sequences, feature deep-dives, and best practice guides that help customers achieve their goals more effectively.' },
      { q: 'How do you determine the right level of depth for educational video?', a: 'Your Creative Director works with your team to define the target audience\'s baseline knowledge and learning objectives. Content is then calibrated to meet viewers where they are: beginner content builds foundational understanding, intermediate content adds nuance, and advanced content addresses edge cases and expert-level concepts.' },
      { q: 'Can educational video content be structured as a course or certification program?', a: 'Yes. Your team produces structured learning paths with progressive modules, knowledge checks, and completion milestones. This format is particularly effective for customer education programs, partner enablement, and thought leadership initiatives that benefit from a curriculum-based approach.' },
      { q: 'How do you make educational content engaging rather than dry?', a: 'Your team uses visual storytelling techniques to keep educational content compelling: dynamic animations that visualize abstract concepts, real-world examples that ground theory in practice, and a pacing structure that alternates between information delivery and visual breaks. The goal is to make learning feel effortless, not like homework.' },
      { q: 'What is the difference between educational video and explainer video?', a: 'Explainer videos focus on communicating what your product does and why it matters, typically in under two minutes. Educational videos go deeper into subject matter, teaching concepts, processes, or skills that your audience values. Educational content builds long-term authority, while explainers drive immediate product understanding.' },
      { q: 'How does educational video content support lead generation?', a: 'Educational content attracts prospects who are actively researching solutions in your category. By providing genuine value through informative video, you build trust and authority that positions your brand as the natural choice when the viewer is ready to buy. Gated educational series and webinar content also capture contact information directly.' },
    ],
    relatedServices: [
      { title: 'Explainer Video Production', slug: 'explainer-video-production', desc: 'Clear, engaging explainer videos from a dedicated creative team.' },
      { title: 'Internal and Training Videos', slug: 'internal-and-training-videos', desc: 'Internal communications and training video at scale.' },
      { title: 'Product Demo Video Production', slug: 'product-demo-video-production', desc: 'Show off your product with demos that get results.' },
    ],
    relatedBlogPosts: [
      { title: 'The complete guide to video production', slug: 'video-production-guide', date: '2026-02-02' },
      { title: 'Video marketing ROI: how to measure what matters', slug: 'video-marketing-roi', date: '2025-10-12' },
    ],
  },

};

const { slug } = Astro.params;
const service = services[slug as string];

function formatDate(dateStr: string): string {
  const d = new Date(dateStr);
  return d.toLocaleDateString('en-GB', { day: 'numeric', month: 'short', year: 'numeric' });
}

const canonicalURL = new URL(`/services/${service.slug}`, Astro.site || 'https://moonb-v2.vercel.app');

const serviceSchema = {
  "@context": "https://schema.org",
  "@type": "Service",
  "name": service.title,
  "description": service.seo.description,
  "provider": { "@type": "Organization", "name": "Moonb", "url": "https://www.moonb.io" },
  "url": canonicalURL.toString(),
};

const breadcrumbSchema = {
  "@context": "https://schema.org",
  "@type": "BreadcrumbList",
  "itemListElement": [
    { "@type": "ListItem", "position": 1, "name": "Home", "item": "https://www.moonb.io" },
    { "@type": "ListItem", "position": 2, "name": "Services", "item": "https://www.moonb.io/services" },
    { "@type": "ListItem", "position": 3, "name": service.title },
  ],
};

const faqSchema = service.faqs?.length ? {
  "@context": "https://schema.org",
  "@type": "FAQPage",
  "mainEntity": service.faqs.map((faq: { q: string; a: string }) => ({
    "@type": "Question",
    "name": faq.q,
    "acceptedAnswer": { "@type": "Answer", "text": faq.a },
  })),
} : null;

const logos = [
  { name: 'Dell', src: 'https://cdn.prod.website-files.com/64c4234d0856ecf478afcf82/691db30dda671fbe474b31d3_Dell_Technologies_logo%201.svg' },
  { name: 'Intel', src: 'https://cdn.prod.website-files.com/64c4234d0856ecf478afcf82/691dca52df40749fbcd69aa5_Intel.svg' },
  { name: 'Toyota', src: 'https://cdn.prod.website-files.com/64c4234d0856ecf478afcf82/6579bef26792b6bec0f6d184_TOYOTA.svg' },
  { name: 'Microsoft', src: 'https://cdn.prod.website-files.com/64c4234d0856ecf478afcf82/6579be8830c130e5738402a3_MICROSOFT.svg' },
  { name: 'Nestlé', src: 'https://cdn.prod.website-files.com/64c4234d0856ecf478afcf82/6579be9467c7bc3dd79a4a1a_NESTLE.svg' },
  { name: 'CyberArk', src: 'https://cdn.prod.website-files.com/64c4234d0856ecf478afcf82/6579bcdba5dd52502ff0dedc_CYBERARK.svg' },
  { name: 'Gnosis', src: 'https://cdn.prod.website-files.com/64c4234d0856ecf478afcf82/6579bcf1769cf9352c288511_GNOSIS.svg' },
  { name: 'State Street', src: 'https://cdn.prod.website-files.com/64c4234d0856ecf478afcf82/6579bedfe6e64721668b66ab_STATESTREET.svg' },
  { name: 'Politico', src: 'https://cdn.prod.website-files.com/64c4234d0856ecf478afcf82/6579bec73f22d633fb4192bb_POLITICO.svg' },
  { name: 'GSK', src: 'https://cdn.prod.website-files.com/64c4234d0856ecf478afcf82/6579bd0d4b4dccecf622b297_GSK.svg' },
];

export function getStaticPaths() {
  return [
    { params: { slug: 'corporate-video-production' } },
    { params: { slug: 'marketing-video-production' } },
    { params: { slug: 'social-media-video-production' } },
    { params: { slug: 'explainer-video-production' } },
    { params: { slug: 'advertising-video-production' } },
    { params: { slug: 'commercial-video-production' } },
    { params: { slug: 'branded-video-production' } },
    { params: { slug: 'promotional-video-production' } },
    { params: { slug: 'product-demo-video-production' } },
    { params: { slug: 'video-series-video-production' } },
    { params: { slug: 'internal-and-training-videos' } },
    { params: { slug: 'educational-video-production' } },
  ];
}
---

<BaseLayout title={service.seo.title} description={service.seo.description}>
  <Fragment slot="head">
    <script type="application/ld+json" set:html={JSON.stringify(serviceSchema)} />
    <script type="application/ld+json" set:html={JSON.stringify(breadcrumbSchema)} />
    {faqSchema && <script type="application/ld+json" set:html={JSON.stringify(faqSchema)} />}
  </Fragment>

  <div class="svc">

    <!-- Breadcrumbs -->
    <div class="svc__container">
      <nav class="svc__breadcrumbs" aria-label="Breadcrumb" data-reveal>
        <a href="/">Home</a>
        <span class="svc__sep">/</span>
        <a href="/services">Services</a>
        <span class="svc__sep">/</span>
        <span>{service.title}</span>
      </nav>
    </div>

    <!-- Hero — 2 column: text left, video right -->
    <section class="svc__hero" data-reveal>
      <div class="svc__container">
        <div class="svc__hero-inner">
          <div class="svc__hero-text">
            <span class="svc__cat">{service.category}</span>
            <h1 class="svc__title">{service.heroHeading}</h1>
            <p class="svc__desc">{service.heroDescription}</p>
            <a href="#work" class="btn btn--secondary">
              <svg class="play-icon" width="12" height="14" viewBox="0 0 12 14" fill="none" aria-hidden="true">
                <path d="M1 1.5C1 0.7 1.9 0.2 2.6 0.6L11 5.8C11.6 6.2 11.6 7.1 11 7.5L2.6 12.7C1.9 13.1 1 12.6 1 11.8V1.5Z" fill="currentColor" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="0.5" stroke-linejoin="round"/>
              </svg>
              See Selected Work
            </a>
          </div>
          <div class="svc__hero-video">
            <div class="svc__video-wrap">
              <iframe src="https://player.vimeo.com/video/1084258404?h=bf1bb4d67b&title=0&byline=0&portrait=0" width="100%" height="100%" style="border:none" allow="autoplay; fullscreen; picture-in-picture" allowfullscreen loading="lazy" title="Moonb Showreel"></iframe>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- Client logos — infinite scroll marquee -->
    <section class="svc__logos">
      <div class="svc__logos-marquee">
        <div class="svc__logos-track">
          {[...logos, ...logos, ...logos].map((logo) => (
            <img src={logo.src} alt={logo.name} class="svc__logo" loading="lazy" />
          ))}
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- What we produce — card grid with numbering -->
    <section class="svc__types section">
      <div class="svc__container">
        <div class="svc__types-header" data-reveal>
          <h2 class="svc__section-heading">What we produce</h2>
          <p class="svc__section-sub">Everything your corporate communications need, from one dedicated team.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="svc__types-grid">
          {service.serviceTypes.map((t, i) => (
            <div class="svc__type-card" data-reveal data-reveal-delay={String(Math.min(i, 5))}>
              <span class="svc__type-num">{String(i + 1).padStart(2, '0')}</span>
              <h3 class="svc__type-title">{t.title}</h3>
              <p class="svc__type-desc">{t.desc}</p>
            </div>
          ))}
        </div>
        <p class="svc__types-more" data-reveal>And much more. If it's video for your business, we produce it.</p>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- Stats strip -->
    <section class="svc__stats">
      <div class="svc__container">
        <div class="svc__stats-grid" data-reveal>
          {service.stats.map((s) => (
            <div class="svc__stat">
              <span class="svc__stat-num">{s.number}</span>
              <span class="svc__stat-label">{s.label}</span>
            </div>
          ))}
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- Differentiator — comparison style -->
    <section class="svc__diff section section--beige">
      <div class="svc__container">
        <div class="svc__diff-inner">
          <div class="svc__diff-text" data-reveal>
            <h2 class="svc__section-heading">{service.differentiator.heading}</h2>
            <p class="svc__diff-body">{service.differentiator.text}</p>
          </div>
          <div class="svc__diff-compare" data-reveal data-reveal-delay="1">
            <div class="svc__compare-table">
              {[0, 1, 2].map((row) => (
                <div class="svc__compare-row">
                  <div class="svc__compare-cell svc__compare-cell--agency">
                    <span class="svc__compare-label">{service.differentiator.points[row * 2].label}</span>
                    <span class="svc__compare-value">{service.differentiator.points[row * 2].value}</span>
                  </div>
                  <div class="svc__compare-vs">vs</div>
                  <div class="svc__compare-cell svc__compare-cell--moonb">
                    <span class="svc__compare-label">{service.differentiator.points[row * 2 + 1].label}</span>
                    <span class="svc__compare-value">{service.differentiator.points[row * 2 + 1].value}</span>
                  </div>
                </div>
              ))}
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- Work — thumbnail grid with play overlay -->
    <section class="svc__work section" id="work">
      <div class="svc__container">
        <h2 class="svc__section-heading" data-reveal>Selected work</h2>
        <div class="svc__work-grid">
          {service.work.map((w, i) => (
            <a href={w.vimeo} target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="svc__work-card" data-reveal data-reveal-delay={String(Math.min(i, 3))}>
              <div class="svc__work-thumb">
                <img src={w.thumb} alt={w.title} loading="lazy" />
                <div class="svc__work-play">
                  <svg width="24" height="24" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none">
                    <path d="M8 5.14v13.72a1 1 0 001.5.86l11.04-6.86a1 1 0 000-1.72L9.5 4.28a1 1 0 00-1.5.86z" fill="#fff"/>
                  </svg>
                </div>
              </div>
              <span class="svc__work-title">{w.title}</span>
            </a>
          ))}
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- Process — horizontal timeline with connecting line -->
    <section class="svc__process section section--beige">
      <div class="svc__container">
        <div class="svc__process-header" data-reveal>
          <h2 class="svc__section-heading">How it works</h2>
          <p class="svc__section-sub">From signup to first delivery in under two weeks.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="svc__process-track">
          <div class="svc__process-line" aria-hidden="true"></div>
          {service.process.map((s, i) => (
            <div class="svc__step" data-reveal data-reveal-delay={String(i)}>
              <div class="svc__step-dot">
                <span class="svc__step-num">{s.number}</span>
              </div>
              <div class="svc__step-content">
                <h3 class="svc__step-title">{s.title}</h3>
                <p class="svc__step-desc">{s.desc}</p>
                <span class="svc__step-detail">{s.detail}</span>
              </div>
            </div>
          ))}
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- Testimonial — large centered quote -->
    <section class="svc__testimonial section">
      <div class="svc__container" data-reveal>
        <div class="svc__quote-mark" aria-hidden="true">"</div>
        <blockquote class="svc__quote">
          <p class="svc__quote-text">{service.testimonial.quote}</p>
          <footer class="svc__quote-footer">
            <img src={service.testimonial.avatar} alt={service.testimonial.name} class="svc__quote-avatar" width="48" height="48" loading="lazy" />
            <div>
              <span class="svc__quote-name">{service.testimonial.name}</span>
              <span class="svc__quote-role">{service.testimonial.role}, {service.testimonial.company}</span>
            </div>
          </footer>
        </blockquote>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- Mid-page CTA banner -->
    <section class="svc__mid-cta">
      <div class="svc__container">
        <div class="svc__mid-cta-inner" data-reveal>
          <h2 class="svc__mid-cta-title">Ready to start producing?</h2>
          <a href="#" class="btn btn--primary" data-cal-link="team/moonb/book-a-demo" data-cal-namespace="book-a-demo" data-cal-config='{"layout":"month_view"}'>Book a Call</a>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- FAQ -->
    {service.faqs?.length > 0 && (
      <section class="svc__faq section section--beige" id="faq">
        <div class="svc__container">
          <div class="faq__inner">
            <div class="faq__left" data-reveal>
              <h2 class="faq__heading">Frequently Asked Questions</h2>
            </div>
            <div class="faq__right">
              <div class="faq__list" data-reveal>
                {service.faqs.map((faq) => (
                  <div class="faq__item" data-faq-item>
                    <button class="faq__question" data-faq-trigger aria-expanded="false">
                      <div class="faq__toggle" aria-hidden="true">
                        <div class="faq__toggle-h"></div>
                        <div class="faq__toggle-v"></div>
                      </div>
                      <span>{faq.q}</span>
                    </button>
                    <div class="faq__answer-wrap" data-faq-answer>
                      <div class="faq__answer"><p>{faq.a}</p></div>
                    </div>
                  </div>
                ))}
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </section>
    )}

    <!-- Related services -->
    <section class="svc__related section">
      <div class="svc__container">
        <div class="svc__related-header" data-reveal>
          <h2 class="svc__section-heading">Related services</h2>
          <a href="/services" class="cta-link" style="color: var(--accent-purple)">All services <svg width="18" height="15" viewBox="0 0 18 15" fill="none" aria-hidden="true"><path d="M1 7.5H17M17 7.5L11 1.5M17 7.5L11 13.5" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.5" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"/></svg></a>
        </div>
        <div class="svc__related-grid">
          {service.relatedServices.map((rs, i) => (
            <a href={`/services/${rs.slug}`} class="svc__related-card" data-reveal data-reveal-delay={String(i)}>
              <h3 class="svc__related-title">{rs.title}</h3>
              <p class="svc__related-desc">{rs.desc}</p>
              <span class="svc__related-arrow">→</span>
            </a>
          ))}
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- Related blog posts -->
    {service.relatedBlogPosts?.length > 0 && (
      <section class="svc__blog section section--beige">
        <div class="svc__container">
          <div class="svc__related-header" data-reveal>
            <h2 class="svc__section-heading">From the blog</h2>
            <a href="/blog" class="cta-link" style="color: var(--accent-green)">All posts <svg width="18" height="15" viewBox="0 0 18 15" fill="none" aria-hidden="true"><path d="M1 7.5H17M17 7.5L11 1.5M17 7.5L11 13.5" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.5" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"/></svg></a>
          </div>
          <div class="svc__blog-grid">
            {service.relatedBlogPosts.map((bp) => (
              <a href={`/blog/${bp.slug}`} class="svc__blog-card" data-reveal>
                <span class="svc__blog-date">{formatDate(bp.date)}</span>
                <h3 class="svc__blog-title">{bp.title}</h3>
              </a>
            ))}
          </div>
        </div>
      </section>
    )}

    <!-- Pre-footer CTA -->
    <section class="final-cta section section--beige">
      <div class="container" data-reveal>
        <div class="final-cta__inner">
          <h2 class="final-cta__title">Ready to level up your creative?</h2>
          <p class="final-cta__sub">Book a call with us. No commitment, no pressure.</p>
          <a href="#" class="cta-link" data-cal-link="team/moonb/book-a-demo" data-cal-namespace="book-a-demo" data-cal-config='{"layout":"month_view"}'>Book a Call <svg width="18" height="15" viewBox="0 0 18 15" fill="none" aria-hidden="true"><path d="M1 7.5H17M17 7.5L11 1.5M17 7.5L11 13.5" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.5" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"/></svg></a>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <Footer />
  </div>
</BaseLayout>

<style>
  /* ==========================================================================
     SERVICE PAGE — v2 redesign
     ========================================================================== */

  .svc__container {
    max-width: calc(var(--max-w) + 3rem);
    margin: 0 auto;
    padding: 0 1.5rem;
  }

  /* Breadcrumbs */
  .svc__breadcrumbs {
    padding-top: 100px;
    margin-bottom: 40px;
    font-size: 13px;
